title: UMD Ends Reign at No. 1, Drops to No. 5
text:
UMD Ends Reign at No. 1, Drops to No. 5 
By Zach Schneider UMD Ends Reign at No. 1, Drops to No. 5 October 12, 2015 Updated Oct 12, 2015 at 3:28 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) volleyball team dropped four spots to No. 5 in this week's American Volleyball Coaches' Association (AVCA) Division II poll, which was released on Monday afternoon. 
The Bulldogs are coming off a (1-2) week in which they lost matches to Concordia-St. Paul and Southwest Minnesota State, and the drop ends a program record four-week stay atop the nationwide poll. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
For full results of this week's AVCA Division II poll, click here. 
UMD is now (14-4) overall this season and will be hosting No. 9 Wayne State and No. 20 Augustana this Friday and Saturday at Romano Gymnasium.
